<section class="about-hero">
    <div class="about-hero-text">
        <h2>Hey, I'm Courtney</h2>
        <p>
            I'm a software engineering student from Zimbabwe, builder of things, and occasional writer.
        </p>
        <p>
            I created CourtNotes as a place to collect thoughts that would otherwise stay stuck in my
            head. Sometimes that's a lesson from a project. Sometimes it's an opinion on a piece of
            technology. Sometimes it's just me trying to make sense of something by writing about it.
        </p>
        <p>
            I won't pretend this blog has a strict publishing schedule.
        </p>
        <p>
            There are weeks when I'll publish several posts, and there are months when I'll disappear
            completely because university, startups, work, or life got in the way. That's just how it is.
        </p>
        <p>
            CourtNotes exists because I like documenting things. Whether I actually get around to
            publishing them is a different story.
        </p>
        <p>
            If you're here for polished tutorials and perfectly planned content calendars, you're
            probably in the wrong place.
        </p>
        <p>
            If you're interested in software engineering, startups, leadership, building products in
            Africa, and the occasional tangent that somehow escaped my notes app, welcome.
        </p>
    </div>
    <div class="about-hero-img">
        <img src="https://courtney-taga.web.app/assets/images/courtney.jpg" alt="Photo of Courtney Fradreck">
    </div>
</section>

<section class="about-content">
    <div class="about-section">
        <h2>What I'm Doing Now</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Building <strong>AgriLease</strong> and growing <strong>DOT</strong> — turning early traction into something that lasts</li>
            <li>Developing <strong>DLM</strong>, a digital lifestyle-medicine platform currently running a live pilot</li>
            <li>Going deep on systems design and scalable software architecture</li>
            <li>Writing more consistently here on CourtNotes — and actually hitting publish</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="about-section">
        <h2>A Few Things About Me</h2>
        <p>
            When I'm not building something, I'm usually plotting how to build it bigger, or thinking
            about tech that actually moves the needle back home. Outside of that, you'll catch me
            reworking a pitch deck, falling down a random research rabbit hole, or with something
            looping in my ears.
        </p>

        <div class="about-gallery">
            <img src="https://placehold.co/600x400/f2f2f7/1c1c1e?text=Coding+Setup" alt="Desk setup with laptop and notebook">
            <img src="https://placehold.co/600x400/f2f2f7/1c1c1e?text=Work+in+Progress" alt="Whiteboard sketches for AgriLease flows">
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="about-section">
        <h2>Why I Write</h2>
        <p>
            The internet has no shortage of polished success stories — the highlight reel where
            everything worked out and the founder always knew it would. I find the in-between far
            more interesting: the wrong turns, the experiments that flopped, the late-night
            debugging, and the occasional win that makes it all worth it.
        </p>
        <p>
            Writing is also how I think things through. Putting a problem into words usually shows me
            where my understanding is thin — so even if a post helps no one else, it's already done
            its job for me. If it happens to help you too, even better.
        </p>
    </div>

    <div class="about-apple-music" data-source="apple-music">
        <h2>On Apple Music</h2>
        <p class="apple-music-intro">
            Kendrick Lamar, Kanye West, Chris Brown, Cassper Nyovest, and JAŸ-Z stay on heavy rotation — and here's
            what that actually looks like in real time.
        </p>

        <div class="apple-music-playlists">
        <div class="apple-music-playlist">
            <div class="apple-music-playlist-head">
                <h3>Recently Played</h3>
                <p>The last few tracks I've had on.</p>
            </div>
            {% if music.recent.length %}
            <ol class="apple-music-tracklist">
                {% for track in music.recent %}
                <li>
                    <a class="apple-music-track" href="{{ track.url }}" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
                        <img src="{{ track.artwork }}" width="56" height="56" loading="lazy" alt="Album artwork for {{ track.name }}">
                        <span class="apple-music-track-info">
                            <span class="apple-music-track-name">{{ track.name }}</span>
                            <span class="apple-music-track-artist">{{ track.artist }}</span>
                        </span>
                    </a>
                </li>
                {% endfor %}
            </ol>
            {% else %}
            <p class="apple-music-note">
                Nothing to show right now — recently played tracks appear here once the Apple Music token is configured and the next build runs.
            </p>
            {% endif %}
        </div>

        {% if music.heavyRotation %}
        <div class="apple-music-playlist">
            <div class="apple-music-playlist-head">
                {% if music.heavyRotation.artwork %}
                <img class="apple-music-playlist-cover" src="{{ music.heavyRotation.artwork }}" width="64" height="64" loading="lazy" alt="{{ music.heavyRotation.name }} playlist cover">
                {% endif %}
                <div>
                    <h3>{{ music.heavyRotation.name }}</h3>
                    <p>
                        My on-repeat playlist, auto-built by Apple Music.
                        {% if music.heavyRotation.url %}<a href="{{ music.heavyRotation.url }}" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Open in Apple Music →</a>{% endif %}
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <ol class="apple-music-tracklist">
                {% for track in music.heavyRotation.tracks %}
                <li>
                    <a class="apple-music-track" href="{{ track.url }}" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
                        <img src="{{ track.artwork }}" width="56" height="56" loading="lazy" alt="Album artwork for {{ track.name }}">
                        <span class="apple-music-track-info">
                            <span class="apple-music-track-name">{{ track.name }}</span>
                            <span class="apple-music-track-artist">{{ track.artist }}</span>
                        </span>
                    </a>
                </li>
                {% endfor %}
            </ol>
        </div>
        {% endif %}
        </div>
